Because it can be against the rules (for example, in the ACBL it is).

Consider another example.  At trick 10 you realize you don't remember
which card you won the opening lead with, so you say &quot;Hey, look at that!&quot;
and while everyone's head is turned up you peek at your played card from
trick 1.  Not only does your partner have no idea of what just happened,
she's the dummy and wouldn't be able to help you if she did.  Did you
cheat?  Of course you did.

Another example, and one that (according to the authorities who expelled
a player for it) has really happened: you bring a deck of cards stacked
with a prepared deal, and surreptitiously swap it for the one that was
in the board.  Partner has no idea what has happened, but you know what's
in everyone's hand.  That's cheating too.
