opener. As far I know, it is perfectly legal to psyche an artifical 2C
that shows a three-suiter

3) Gary Blaise who was ACBL CTD at the time, indicated in answering my
inquiry about a particular use of a 2C opener that &quot;the term 'strong'
was intentionally not tied to a specific number of high card points in
some cases because shapely hands are considered 'strong' by some
players. I don't think that anyone could disagree that 15 HCP is
'strong'&quot;

